Advantages of Stored Procedures

• Faster execution
• Reusable SQL code
• Reduces code duplication
• Improves security
• Easier maintenance

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Disadvantages of Stored Procedures

• Difficult to debug
• Increased database load
• Complex procedures are harder to manage

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important Points

• Stored Procedure is a group of SQL statements.
• Stored inside database server.
• Executed using CALL statement.
• Supports input parameters.
• Helps automate database operations.

