28. Explain the difference between UNION and UNION ALL.

Answer

UNION and UNION ALL are SQL operators used to combine results from two or more SELECT statements.

The main difference is that UNION removes duplicate records, whereas UNION ALL includes all records including duplicates.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

UNION

• Combines results from multiple SELECT statements
• Removes duplicate rows
• Returns only unique records
• Slower because duplicate checking is performed

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

UNION ALL

• Combines results from multiple SELECT statements
• Includes duplicate rows
• Returns all records
• Faster because duplicate checking is not performed

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Rules for UNION and UNION ALL

• Number of columns must be same in all SELECT statements
• Data types of columns should be compatible
• Column order should be same

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax of UNION

SELECT column_name
FROM table_name

UNION

SELECT column_name
FROM table_name;

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example of UNION

SELECT department
FROM employees

UNION

SELECT department
FROM managers;

Explanation

• Combines department names from both tables.
• Duplicate department names are removed.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax of UNION ALL

SELECT column_name
FROM table_name

UNION ALL

SELECT column_name
FROM table_name;

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example of UNION ALL

SELECT department
FROM employees

UNION ALL

SELECT department
FROM managers;

Explanation

• Combines all department names including duplicates.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Real-Time Example

Consider two tables.

Employees Table

Department
IT
HR
Finance

Managers Table

Department
IT
Admin

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

UNION Example

SELECT department
FROM employees

UNION

SELECT department
FROM managers;

Output

IT
HR
Finance
Admin

Explanation

• Duplicate value IT appears only once.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

UNION ALL Example

SELECT department
FROM employees

UNION ALL

SELECT department
FROM managers;

Output

IT
HR
Finance
IT
Admin

Explanation

• Duplicate value IT appears twice.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Key Differences

UNION
• Removes duplicate rows
• Returns unique records
• Slower performance
• Performs duplicate checking

UNION ALL
• Includes duplicate rows
• Returns all records
• Faster performance
• No duplicate checking

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important Points

• UNION removes duplicate records.
• UNION ALL keeps duplicate records.
• UNION ALL is faster than UNION.
• Column count and datatype must match.
• Both are used to combine results from multiple SELECT queries.

