29. What is a Composite Key?

Answer

A Composite Key in MySQL is a combination of two or more columns used together to uniquely identify each row in a table.

A single column alone cannot uniquely identify records, so multiple columns are combined to form a unique key.

Composite Keys are commonly used in junction tables and many-to-many relationships.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Features of Composite Key

• Combination of multiple columns
• Uniquely identifies each row
• Prevents duplicate records
• Used when one column is not sufficient
• Can contain two or more columns

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Why Composite Key is Used

• Ensures uniqueness using multiple columns
• Maintains data integrity
• Used in many-to-many relationships
• Reduces duplicate data
• Improves relational database design

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax of Composite Key

CREATE TABLE table_name (
    column1 datatype,
    column2 datatype,
    PRIMARY KEY (column1, column2)
);

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example of Composite Key

CREATE TABLE student_courses (
    student_id INT,
    course_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (student_id, course_id)
);

Explanation

• Combination of student_id and course_id uniquely identifies each record.
• Duplicate combinations are not allowed.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Real-Time Example

Consider a Student_Courses Table.

Student_ID      Course_ID
101             C001
101             C002
102             C001

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Valid Insert

INSERT INTO student_courses
VALUES (101, 'C003');

Explanation

• Combination (101, C003) is unique.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Invalid Insert

INSERT INTO student_courses
VALUES (101, 'C001');

Output

Error: Duplicate entry

Explanation

• Combination (101, C001) already exists.
• Composite Key prevents duplicate combinations.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Composite Key in Many-to-Many Relationship

Students Table
• student_id
• student_name

Courses Table
• course_id
• course_name

Student_Courses Table
• student_id
• course_id

Explanation

• One student can enroll in many courses.
• One course can have many students.
• Composite Key helps manage relationship efficiently.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Advantages of Composite Key

• Ensures uniqueness across multiple columns
• Maintains data consistency
• Useful in relationship tables
• Prevents duplicate combinations

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Disadvantages of Composite Key

• Increases query complexity
• Larger key size affects performance
• Difficult to manage in large databases

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important Points

• Composite Key combines multiple columns.
• Used when single column is not unique.
• Defined using PRIMARY KEY(column1, column2).
• Commonly used in junction tables.
• Helps maintain relational integrity.

